🚗 Road Accident Prediction Using Machine Learning
1. Objective

The goal of the project is to predict whether a road accident is likely to occur based on different conditions such as:

Weather condition

Road condition

Time of day

Traffic density

Speed

Visibility

Machine learning models analyze past accident data and learn patterns to predict future accidents.

2. Technologies Used

Python

Pandas – Data processing

NumPy – Numerical operations

Scikit-learn – Machine learning models

Matplotlib / Seaborn – Data visualization

Jupyter Notebook / Google Colab

3. Dataset Example

Example dataset columns:

Weather	Road_Type	Traffic	Speed	Visibility	Accident
Rainy	Highway	High	80	Low	1
Clear	City	Low	40	High	0
Fog	Highway	Medium	60	Low	1

Where

1 = Accident occurred

0 = No accident

